-- Mexico Stocks: ICA, Penoles, Minera Frisco, Grupo Mexico, Gruma
-- B y   J o s e   E n r i q u e   A r r i o j a
-- 2011-12-28T22:12:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/mexico-stocks-ica-penoles-minera-frisco-grupo-mexico-gruma.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC  index (MEXBOL)  fell 1.2 percent to 36,644.86, its biggest
decline since Dec. 19.  Mexican mining companies declined on prospects for lower
demand in India and  China . Oil, copper, gold and silver prices
fell. Retailers also declined.  Industrias Penoles (PE&OLES* MM), the nation’s biggest
silver producer, fell 2.2 percent to 599.94 pesos after the
metal declined 5.5 percent to $27.115 an ounce.  Minera Frisco (MFRISCOA MM), the mining company controlled
by billionaire  Carlos Slim , retreated 2.4 percent to 50.09
pesos.  Grupo Mexico  SAB (GMEXICOB MM), the country’s largest
mining company, fell 1.4 percent to 36.63 pesos.  Empresas ICA (ICA*)  , Mexico’s largest construction
company, dropped 3.7 percent to 17.12 pesos. ICA has teamed up
with Irving, Texas-based  Fluor Corporation (FLR)  to bid on the
building of a $9 billion refinery in central Mexico, daily
newspaper  El Universal  reported.  Gruma SAB (GRUMAB)  , Mexico’s largest maker of corn flour
for tortillas, fell for second day, losing 0.6 percent to 25.93
pesos. Corn for March delivery rose 1.5 percent to $6.4250 a
bushel on the Chicago Board of Trade, an eighth straight gain.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jose Enrique Arrioja in Mexico City at 
